rogrammer. You will be given a question (problem specification) and will generate a correct Python program that matches the specification and passes all tests.\n\n### Question:\nGiven an array of integers nums and an integer k, return the total number of subarrays whose sum equals to k.\nA subarray is a contiguous non-empty sequence of elements within an array.\n \nExample 1:\nInput: nums = [1,1,1], k = 2\nOutput: 2\nExample 2:\nInput: nums = [1,2,3], k = 3\nOutput: 2\n\n \nConstraints:\n\n1 <= nums.length <= 2 * 104\n-1000 <= nums[i] <= 1000\n-107 <= k <= 107\n\n\n\n### Format: You will use the following starter code to write the solution to the problem and enclose your code within delimiters.\n```python\nclass Solution:\n    def subarraySum(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def subarraySum(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:\n        # Dictionary to store the cumulative sum frequencies\n        cumulative_sum_map = {0: 1}\n        current_sum = 0\n        count = 0\n        \n        for num in nums:\n            current_sum += num\n            # Check if there is a subarray (ending at the current index) which sums to k\n            if (current_sum - k) in cumulative_sum_map:\n                count += cumulative_sum_map[current_sum - k]\n            \n            # Update the cumulative sum map\n            if current_sum in cumulative_sum_map:\n                cumulative_sum_map[current_sum] += 1\n            else:\n                cumulative_sum_map[current_sum] = 1\n        \n        return count\n```\n\nThis solution uses a hash map (dictionary) to store the cumulative sum frequencies as we iterate through the array. This allows us to efficiently check how many times the sum `current_sum - k` has occurred, which indicates that there is a subarray ending at the current index that sums to `k`. The solution has a time complexity of O(n), where n is the length of the array, and a space complexity of O(n) due to the hash map.", "estimated_date": 1438905600000}